WEBVTT

00:00:22.160 --> 00:00:52.140
The former treaties have I made, O Theophilus, of all that Jesus began both to do and teach, until the day in which he was taken up, after that he, through the Holy Ghost, had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen, to whom also he showed himself alive after his passion by many infallible proofs, being seen of them forty days, and speaking of the things pertaining to the kingdom of God.

00:00:52.140 --> 00:01:14.460
And, being assembled together with them, commanded them that they should not depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the Father, which, saith he, ye have heard of me. For John truly baptized with water, but ye shall be baptized with the Holy Ghost not many days hence.

00:01:15.320 --> 00:01:41.040
When they, therefore, were come together, they asked of him, saying, Lord, wilt thou at this time restore again the kingdom to Israel? And he said unto them, It is not for you to know the times or the seasons which the Father hath put in his own power, but ye shall receive power, after that the Holy Ghost is come upon you.

00:01:41.040 --> 00:01:51.660
And ye shall be witnesses unto me both in Jerusalem, and in all Judea, and in Samaria, and unto the uttermost part of the earth.

00:01:52.360 --> 00:02:18.180
And when he had spoken these things, while they beheld, he was taken up, and a cloud received him out of their sight. And while they looked steadfastly toward heaven as he went up, behold, two men stood by them in white apparel, which also said, Ye men of Galilee, why stand ye gazing up into heaven?

00:02:18.180 --> 00:02:28.820
The same Jesus, which is taken up from you into heaven, shall so come in like manner as ye have seen him go into heaven.

00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:57.380
Then returned they unto Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is from Jerusalem a Sabbath-day's journey. And when they were come in, they went up into an upper room, where abode both Peter and James and John and Andrew, Philip and Thomas, Bartholomew and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon's Elotes, and Judas the brother of James.

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:18.840
These all continued, with one accord in prayer and supplication, with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brethren. And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples, and said, The number of names together were about 120.

00:03:19.860 --> 00:03:40.980
Men and brethren, this scripture must needs have been fulfilled, which the Holy Ghost by the mouth of David spake before concerning Judas, which was guide to them that took Jesus. For he was numbered with us, and had obtained part of this ministry.

00:03:40.980 --> 00:03:53.440
Now this man purchased a field with the reward of iniquity, and falling headlong, he burst asunder in the midst, and all his bowels gushed out.

00:03:54.660 --> 00:04:19.560
And it was known unto all the dwellers of Jerusalem insomuch as that field is called in their proper tongue a Keldema, that is to say the field of blood. For it is written in the book of Psalms, Let his habitation be desolate, And let no man dwell therein, And his bishopric let another take.

00:04:20.620 --> 00:04:38.100
Wherefore of these men, which have accompanied with us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us, beginning from the baptism of John, unto the same day that he was taken up from us, must one be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection.

00:04:39.680 --> 00:05:07.220
And they appointed to Joseph called Barsabbas, who was surname Justus, and Mathias. And they prayed and said, Thou Lord, which knowest the hearts of all men, show whether of these two thou hast chosen, that he may take part of this ministry and apostleship, from which Judas by transgression fell, that he might go to his own place.

00:05:08.780 --> 00:05:17.880
And they gave forth their lots, and the lot fell upon Mathias, and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.

00:05:20.500 --> 00:05:37.640
And when the day of Pentecost was fully come, they were all with one accord in one place. And suddenly there came a sound from heaven as of a rushing mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.

00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:56.620
And there appeared unto them cloven tongues like as a fire, and it sat upon each of them. And they were all filled with the Holy Ghost, and began to speak with other tongues, as the Spirit gave them utterance.

00:05:57.300 --> 00:06:14.700
And there were dwelling at Jerusalem Jews, devout men, out of every nation under heaven. Now when this was noised abroad, the multitude came together and were confounded, because that every man heard them speak in his own language.

00:06:15.460 --> 00:06:31.320
And they were all amazed and marvelled, saying one to another, Behold, are not all these which speak Galileans? And how hear we every man in our own tongue, wherein we were born?

00:06:32.660 --> 00:07:00.980
Parthians and Medes and Elamites, and the dwellers in Mesopotamia, and in Judea and Cappadocia and Pontius, and Asia, Phrygia and Pamphylia, in Egypt, and in the parts of Libya about Cyrene, and strangers of Rome, Jews and proselytes, Cretes and Arabians, we do hear them speak in our tongues, the wonderful works of God.

00:07:01.320 --> 00:07:08.080
And they were all amazed, and were in doubt, saying one to another, What meaneth this?

00:07:09.900 --> 00:07:14.820
Others mocking said, These men are full of new wine.

00:07:16.220 --> 00:07:31.660
But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice, and said unto them, Ye men of Judea, and all ye that dwell at Jerusalem, be this known unto you and hearken to my words.

00:07:32.460 --> 00:07:38.640
For these are not drunken, as ye suppose, seeing it is but the third hour of the day.

00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:42.880
But this is that which was spoken by the prophet Joel.

00:07:43.880 --> 00:07:53.900
And it shall come to pass, In the last days saith God, I will pour out of my spirit upon all flesh.

00:07:54.580 --> 00:08:04.040
And your sons and your daughters shall prophesy, And your young men shall see visions, And your old men shall dream dreams.

00:08:05.540 --> 00:08:15.100
And on my servants, and on my handmaidens, I will pour out in those days of my spirit, And they shall prophesy.

00:08:16.440 --> 00:08:25.320
And I will show wonders in heaven above, And signs in the earth beneath, Blood and fire and vapor of smoke.

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:35.180
The sun shall be turned into darkness, And the moon into blood, Before the great and notable day of the Lord come.

00:08:35.860 --> 00:08:42.720
And it shall come to pass, That whosoever shall call on the name of the Lord shall be saved.

00:08:43.720 --> 00:08:46.040
Ye men of Israel, hear these words.

00:08:47.020 --> 00:08:53.820
Jesus of Nazareth, a man approved of God among you by miracles and wonders and signs,

00:08:54.280 --> 00:08:59.480
which God did by him in the midst of you, as ye yourselves also know.

00:09:00.480 --> 00:09:08.080
Him, being delivered by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God, ye have taken,

00:09:08.440 --> 00:09:14.860
and by wicked hands have crucified and slain, whom God hath raised up.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:23.880
Having loosed the pains of death, because it was not possible that he should beholden of it.

00:09:25.260 --> 00:09:31.800
For David speaketh concerning him. I foresaw the Lord always before my face,

00:09:32.840 --> 00:09:36.960
for he is on my right hand that I should not be moved.

00:09:38.140 --> 00:09:42.760
Therefore did my heart rejoice, and my tongue was glad.

00:09:43.640 --> 00:09:47.860
Moreover, also my flesh shall rest in hope.

00:09:49.040 --> 00:09:56.540
Because thou wilt not leave my soul in hell, neither wilt thou suffer thine holy one to seek corruption.

00:09:58.780 --> 00:10:07.060
Thou hast made known to me the ways of life. Thou shalt make me full of joy with thy countenance.

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:13.300
Men and brethren, let me freely speak unto you of the patriarch David,

00:10:14.480 --> 00:10:19.280
that he is both dead and buried, and his supplicer is with us unto this day.

00:10:20.480 --> 00:10:26.740
Therefore, being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him,

00:10:27.500 --> 00:10:34.260
that of the fruit of his loins according to the flesh he would raise up Christ to sit on his throne,

00:10:35.480 --> 00:10:40.560
he, seeing this before, spake of the resurrection of Christ,

00:10:41.560 --> 00:10:46.520
that his soul was not left in hell, neither his flesh did seek corruption.

00:10:47.720 --> 00:10:53.640
This Jesus hath God raised up, whereof we all are witnesses.

00:10:54.360 --> 00:11:02.360
Therefore, being by the right hand of God exalted, and having received of the Father the promise of the Holy Ghost,

00:11:02.360 --> 00:11:08.060
he hath shed forth this, which ye now see and hear.

00:11:09.100 --> 00:11:13.420
For David is not ascended into the heavens, but he saith himself,

00:11:14.520 --> 00:11:22.520
The Lord said unto my Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, until I make thy foes thy footstool.

00:11:23.940 --> 00:11:30.420
Therefore, let all the house of Israel know assuredly that God hath made the same Jesus,

00:11:30.420 --> 00:11:35.100
whom ye have crucified, both Lord and Christ.

00:11:36.100 --> 00:11:41.480
Now when they heard this, they were pricked in their heart, and said unto Peter,

00:11:41.760 --> 00:11:45.780
and to the rest of the apostles, Men and brethren, what shall we do?

00:11:46.140 --> 00:11:54.640
Then Peter said unto them, Repent, and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ,

00:11:54.640 --> 00:12:00.520
for the remission of sins, and ye shall receive the gift of the Holy Ghost.

00:12:01.460 --> 00:12:10.880
For the promise is unto you, and to your children, and to all that are afar off, even as many as the Lord our God shall call.

00:12:12.500 --> 00:12:17.220
And with many other words did he testify, and exhort, saying,

00:12:17.220 --> 00:12:21.390
Save yourselves from this untoward generation.

00:12:22.820 --> 00:12:32.060
Then they that gladly received his word were baptized, and the same day there were added unto them about three thousand souls.

00:12:33.540 --> 00:12:41.260
And they continued steadfastly in the apostles' doctrine, and fellowship, and in breaking of bread, and in prayers.

00:12:41.260 --> 00:12:48.520
And fear came upon every soul, and many wonders and signs were done by the apostles.

00:12:49.660 --> 00:13:02.640
And all that believed were together, and had all things common, and sold their possessions and goods, and parted them to all men, as every man had need.

00:13:03.340 --> 00:13:18.580
And they, continuing daily with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread from house to house, did eat their meat with gladness and singleness of heart, praising God, and having favor with all the people.

00:13:19.220 --> 00:13:23.840
And the Lord added to the church daily, such as should be saved.

00:13:26.440 --> 00:13:33.080
Now Peter and John went up together into the temple at the hour of prayer, being the ninth hour.

00:13:33.780 --> 00:13:45.440
And a certain lame man from his mother's womb was carried, whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple, which is called Beautiful, to ask alms of them that entered into the temple.

00:13:45.440 --> 00:13:50.660
Who, seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple, asked in alms.

00:13:51.780 --> 00:13:58.340
And Peter, fastening his eyes upon him with John, said, Look on us.

00:13:59.260 --> 00:14:03.640
And he gave heed unto them, expecting to receive something of them.

00:14:04.620 --> 00:14:08.780
Then Peter said, Silver and gold have I none.

00:14:09.660 --> 00:14:12.660
But such as I have, give I thee.

00:14:12.660 --> 00:14:18.360
In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, rise up and walk.

00:14:20.280 --> 00:14:29.000
And he took him by the right hand, and lifted him up, and immediately his feet and ankle bones received strength.

00:14:30.060 --> 00:14:38.560
And he, leaping up, stood and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking and leaping and praising God.

00:14:40.220 --> 00:14:44.340
And all the people saw him, walking and praising God.

00:14:44.880 --> 00:14:50.480
And they knew that it was he which sat for alms at the beautiful gate of the temple.

00:14:51.040 --> 00:14:57.020
And they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened unto him.

00:14:57.780 --> 00:15:06.620
And as the lame man which was healed held Peter and John, all the people ran together unto them in the porch that is called Solomon's.

00:15:07.640 --> 00:15:08.820
Greatly wondering.

00:15:10.680 --> 00:15:17.880
And when Peter saw it, he answered unto the people, Ye men of Israel, why marvel ye at this?

00:15:18.440 --> 00:15:27.440
Why look ye so earnestly on us, as though by our own power or holiness we had made this man to walk?

00:15:27.440 --> 00:15:38.260
The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, hath glorified his son Jesus, whom ye delivered up,

00:15:38.780 --> 00:15:44.540
and denied him in the presence of Pilate, when he was determined to let him go.

00:15:44.920 --> 00:15:53.120
But ye denied the Holy One, and the Just, and desired a murderer to be granted unto you,

00:15:53.120 --> 00:16:01.100
and killed the Prince of Life, whom God hath raised from the dead, whereof we are witnesses.

00:16:02.120 --> 00:16:09.400
And his name, through faith in his name, hath made this man strong, whom ye see and know,

00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:18.200
yea, the faith which is by him hath given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.

00:16:18.200 --> 00:16:24.820
And now, brethren, I want that through ignorance ye did it, as did also your rulers.

00:16:25.260 --> 00:16:34.620
But those things which God before had shewed by the mouth of all his prophets, that Christ should suffer, he hath so fulfilled.

00:16:35.640 --> 00:16:41.520
Repent ye therefore, and be converted, that your sins may be blotted out,

00:16:41.520 --> 00:16:49.600
when the times of refreshing shall come from the presence of the Lord, and he shall send Jesus Christ,

00:16:50.580 --> 00:16:58.160
which before was preached unto you, whom the heaven must receive until the times of restitution of all things,

00:16:58.640 --> 00:17:04.400
which God hath spoken by the mouth of all his holy prophets since the world began.

00:17:04.400 --> 00:17:14.440
For Moses truly said unto the fathers, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren like unto me,

00:17:15.020 --> 00:17:19.480
him shall ye hear in all things whatsoever he shall say unto you.

00:17:19.640 --> 00:17:27.740
And it shall come to pass that every soul which will not hear that prophet shall be destroyed from among the people,

00:17:27.740 --> 00:17:37.830
yea, and all the prophets from Samuel and those that follow after, as many as have spoken, have likewise foretold of these days.

00:17:38.920 --> 00:17:45.010
Ye are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers,

00:17:45.880 --> 00:17:52.420
saying unto Abraham, And in thy seed shall all the kindreds of the earth be blessed.

00:17:52.420 --> 00:18:03.540
Unto you first, God, having raised up his son Jesus, sent him to bless you, and turning away every one of you from his iniquities.

00:18:06.380 --> 00:18:07.020
4.

00:18:26.720 --> 00:18:33.260
And as they spake unto the people, the priests, and the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees

00:18:33.260 --> 00:18:39.600
came upon them, being grieved that they taught the people, and preached through Jesus the

00:18:39.600 --> 00:18:41.220
resurrection from the dead.

00:18:41.840 --> 00:18:47.400
And they laid hands on them, and put them in hold unto the next day, for it was now

00:18:47.400 --> 00:18:48.380
even tide.

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:55.320
Howbeit many of them which heard the word believed, and the number of the men was about

00:18:55.320 --> 00:18:56.220
five thousand.

00:18:57.060 --> 00:19:03.560
And it came to pass on the morrow, that their rulers, and elders, and scribes, and Annas

00:19:03.560 --> 00:19:10.460
the high priest, and Caiaphas, and John, and Alexander, and as many as were of the kindred

00:19:10.460 --> 00:19:14.100
of the high priest, were gathered together at Jerusalem.

00:19:14.640 --> 00:19:21.960
And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name have

00:19:21.960 --> 00:19:22.980
ye done this?

00:19:22.980 --> 00:19:31.600
Then Peter, filled with the Holy Ghost, said unto them, Ye rulers of the people, and elders

00:19:31.600 --> 00:19:40.620
of Israel, If we this day be examined of the good deed done to the impotent man, by what

00:19:40.620 --> 00:19:49.100
means he is made whole, be it known unto you all, and to all the people of Israel, that

00:19:49.100 --> 00:19:57.000
by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom ye crucified, whom God raised from the dead,

00:19:57.380 --> 00:20:01.860
even by him doth this man stand here before you whole.

00:20:02.920 --> 00:20:10.880
This is the stone, which was set at naught of you builders, which is become the head

00:20:10.880 --> 00:20:17.900
of the corner, neither is there salvation in any other, for there is none other name

00:20:17.900 --> 00:20:22.460
under heaven given among men, whereby we must be saved.

00:20:23.740 --> 00:20:30.260
Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned

00:20:30.260 --> 00:20:33.500
and ignorant men, they marveled.

00:20:33.860 --> 00:20:40.060
And they took knowledge of them, that they had been with Jesus, and beholding the man

00:20:40.060 --> 00:20:45.080
which was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.

00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:52.000
But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council, they conferred among

00:20:52.000 --> 00:20:56.200
themselves, saying, What shall we do to these men?

00:20:56.620 --> 00:21:02.340
For that indeed a notable miracle hath been done by them is manifest to all them that

00:21:02.340 --> 00:21:05.300
dwell in Jerusalem, and we cannot deny it.

00:21:05.880 --> 00:21:12.340
But that it spread no further among the people, let us straightly threaten them, that they

00:21:12.340 --> 00:21:15.600
speak henceforth to no man in this name.

00:21:16.380 --> 00:21:23.920
And they called them, and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus.

00:21:24.920 --> 00:21:30.700
But Peter and John answered and said unto them, Whether it be right in the sight of

00:21:30.700 --> 00:21:34.820
God to hearken unto you more than unto God, judge ye.

00:21:35.540 --> 00:21:40.200
For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.

00:21:40.900 --> 00:21:46.060
So when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding nothing how they

00:21:46.060 --> 00:21:48.420
might punish them, because of the people.

00:21:48.800 --> 00:21:52.080
For all men glorified God for that which was done.

00:21:53.040 --> 00:21:58.960
For the man was above forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was shewed, and

00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:06.140
being let go, they went to their own company, and reported all that the chief priests and

00:22:06.140 --> 00:22:08.080
elders had said unto them.

00:22:08.920 --> 00:22:15.540
And when they heard that, they lifted up their voice to God, with one accord, and said,

00:22:15.900 --> 00:22:25.580
Lord, thou art God, which hast made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that in them

00:22:25.580 --> 00:22:33.640
is, who by the mouth of thy servant David hast said, Why did the heathen rage?

00:22:34.200 --> 00:22:37.180
And the people imagined vain things.

00:22:37.720 --> 00:22:44.160
The kings of the earth stood up, and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord, and

00:22:44.160 --> 00:22:45.620
against his Christ.

00:22:47.460 --> 00:22:55.040
For of a truth against thy holy child Jesus, whom thou hast anointed, both Herod and Pontius

00:22:55.040 --> 00:23:01.440
Pilate with the Gentiles and the people of Israel were gathered together, for to do whatsoever

00:23:01.440 --> 00:23:05.460
thy hand and thy counsel determined before to be done.

00:23:06.680 --> 00:23:13.240
And now, Lord, behold their threatenings, and grant unto thy servants, that with all

00:23:13.240 --> 00:23:20.480
boldness they may speak thy word, by stretching forth thine hand to heal, and that signs and

00:23:20.480 --> 00:23:24.480
wonders may be done by the name of thy holy child Jesus.

00:23:25.040 --> 00:23:31.800
And when they had prayed, the place was shaken where they were assembled together, and they

00:23:31.800 --> 00:23:38.780
were all filled with the Holy Ghost, and they spake the word of God with boldness.

00:23:39.860 --> 00:23:46.500
And the multitude of them that believed were of one heart and of one soul, neither said

00:23:46.500 --> 00:23:52.200
any of them that ought of the things which he possessed was his own, but they had all

00:23:52.200 --> 00:23:58.720
common, and with great power gave the apostles witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus,

00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:02.320
and great grace was upon them all.

00:24:03.180 --> 00:24:08.860
Neither was there any among them that lacked, for as many as were possessors of lands or

00:24:08.860 --> 00:24:15.540
houses sold them, and brought the prices of the things that were sold, and laid them down

00:24:15.540 --> 00:24:21.680
at the apostles' feet, and distribution was made unto every man according as he had need.

00:24:22.260 --> 00:24:28.900
And Joses, who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas, which is being interpreted the son

00:24:28.900 --> 00:24:37.060
of Consolation, a Levite, and of the country of Cyprus, having land, sold it, and brought

00:24:37.060 --> 00:24:40.180
the money, and laid it at the apostles' feet.

00:24:40.700 --> 00:24:46.060
But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira

00:24:46.060 --> 00:24:53.640
his wife, sold a possession, and kept back part of the price, his wife also being privy

00:24:53.640 --> 00:24:58.760
to it, and brought a certain part, and laid it at the apostles' feet.

00:24:59.300 --> 00:25:08.420
But Peter said, Ananias, why hath Satan filled thine heart to lie to the Holy Ghost, and

00:25:08.420 --> 00:25:11.460
to keep back part of the price of the land?

00:25:12.120 --> 00:25:14.820
Whilst it remained, was it not thine own?

00:25:15.040 --> 00:25:19.120
And after it was sold, was it not in thine own power?

00:25:19.740 --> 00:25:22.740
Why hast thou conceived this thing in thine heart?

00:25:23.160 --> 00:25:27.560
Thou hast not lied unto men, but unto God.

00:25:28.540 --> 00:25:36.500
And Ananias, hearing these words, fell down, and gave up the Ghost, and great fear came

00:25:36.500 --> 00:25:39.100
on all them that heard these things.

00:25:40.120 --> 00:25:46.180
And the young men arose, wound him up, and carried him out, and buried him.

00:25:46.880 --> 00:25:52.800
And it was about the space of three hours after, when his wife, not knowing what was

00:25:52.800 --> 00:26:00.300
done, came in, and Peter answered unto her, Tell me, whether ye sold the land for so much?

00:26:01.300 --> 00:26:03.360
And she said, Yea, for so much.

00:26:04.160 --> 00:26:10.980
Then Peter said unto her, How is it that ye have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of

00:26:10.980 --> 00:26:11.820
the Lord?

00:26:12.140 --> 00:26:18.540
Behold, the feet of them which have buried thy husband are at the door, and shall carry

00:26:18.540 --> 00:26:19.620
thee out.

00:26:20.420 --> 00:26:25.600
Then fell she down, straightway at his feet, and yielded up the Ghost.

00:26:25.900 --> 00:26:33.340
And the young men came in, and found her dead, and carrying her forth, buried her by her

00:26:33.340 --> 00:26:33.760
husband.

00:26:34.940 --> 00:26:41.320
And great fear came upon all the church, and upon as many as heard these things.

00:26:42.120 --> 00:26:47.460
And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders wrought among the people.

00:26:48.340 --> 00:26:51.940
And they were all with one accord in Solomon's porch.

00:26:52.680 --> 00:26:59.100
And of the rest there's no man joined himself to them, but the people magnified them.

00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:07.100
And believers were the more added to the Lord multitudes both of men and women, insomuch

00:27:07.100 --> 00:27:12.920
that they brought forth the sick into the streets, and laid them on beds and couches,

00:27:13.300 --> 00:27:18.520
that at the least the shadow of Peter passing by might overshadow some of them.

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:25.040
There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem, bringing sick

00:27:25.720 --> 00:27:29.400
and them which were vexed with unclean spirits.

00:27:30.320 --> 00:27:32.200
And they were healed every one.

00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:38.540
Then the high priest rose up, and all they that were with him, which is the sect of the

00:27:38.540 --> 00:27:45.500
Sadducees, and were filled with indignation, and laid their hands on the apostles, and

00:27:45.500 --> 00:27:47.320
put them in the common prison.

00:27:48.040 --> 00:27:54.400
But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors, and brought them forth,

00:27:54.920 --> 00:28:01.920
and said, Go, stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.

00:28:02.380 --> 00:28:07.600
And when they heard that, they entered into the temple early in the morning, and taught.

00:28:08.280 --> 00:28:13.920
But the high priest came, and they that were with him, and called the council together,

00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:20.460
and all the senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.

00:28:21.880 --> 00:28:28.520
But when the officers came, and found them not in the prison, they returned and told,

00:28:28.720 --> 00:28:36.160
saying, The prison truly found we shut, with all safety, and the keepers standing without

00:28:36.160 --> 00:28:37.300
before the doors.

00:28:37.660 --> 00:28:41.460
But when we had opened, we found no man within.

00:28:42.340 --> 00:28:47.520
Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple, and the chief priests heard these

00:28:47.520 --> 00:28:51.300
things, they doubted of them whereunto this would grow.

00:28:52.700 --> 00:28:59.060
Then came one, and told them, saying, Behold, the men whom ye put in prison, are standing

00:28:59.060 --> 00:29:01.660
in the temple, and teaching the people.

00:29:02.460 --> 00:29:07.180
Then went the captain with the officers, and brought them without violence, for they feared

00:29:07.180 --> 00:29:09.580
the people, lest they should have been stoned.

00:29:10.180 --> 00:29:15.240
And when they had brought them, they set them before the council, and the high priest asked

00:29:15.240 --> 00:29:20.640
them, saying, Did not we straightly command you that ye should not teach in this name?

00:29:20.800 --> 00:29:28.720
And behold, ye have filled Jerusalem with your doctrine, and intend to bring this man's

00:29:28.720 --> 00:29:30.140
blood upon us.

00:29:30.600 --> 00:29:36.960
Then Peter and the other apostles answered, and said, We ought to obey God rather than

00:29:36.960 --> 00:29:37.440
men.

00:29:37.900 --> 00:29:44.040
The God of our fathers raised up Jesus, whom ye slew, and hanged on a tree.

00:29:44.560 --> 00:29:53.100
Him hath God exalted with his right hand, to be a prince and a savior, for to give repentance

00:29:53.100 --> 00:29:56.180
to Israel, and forgiveness of sins.

00:29:57.120 --> 00:30:05.220
And we are his witnesses of these things, and so is also the Holy Ghost, whom God hath

00:30:05.220 --> 00:30:07.260
given to them that obey him.

00:30:08.720 --> 00:30:14.640
When they heard that, they were cut to the heart, and took counsel to slay them.

00:30:15.120 --> 00:30:23.360
Then stood thereup one in the council, a Pharisee named Gamaliel, a doctor of the law, had in

00:30:23.360 --> 00:30:29.780
reputation among all the people, and commanded to put the apostles forth a little space,

00:30:29.980 --> 00:30:36.980
and said unto them, Ye men of Israel, take heed to yourselves what ye intend to do as

00:30:36.980 --> 00:30:38.300
touching these men.

00:30:39.020 --> 00:30:46.060
For before these days rose up Theodos, boasting himself to be somebody, to whom a number of

00:30:46.060 --> 00:30:53.700
men about four hundred joined themselves, who was slain, and all as many as obeyed him

00:30:53.700 --> 00:30:56.160
were scattered and brought to naught.

00:30:57.040 --> 00:31:04.400
After this man rose up Judas of Galilee, in the days of the taxing, and drew away much

00:31:04.400 --> 00:31:05.760
people after him.

00:31:06.580 --> 00:31:13.320
He also perished, and all, even as many as obeyed him, were dispersed.

00:31:13.840 --> 00:31:20.020
And now I say unto you, Refrain from these men, and let them alone.

00:31:20.020 --> 00:31:25.820
For if this council, or this work be of men, it will come to naught.

00:31:27.020 --> 00:31:35.560
But if it be of God, ye cannot overthrow it, lest happily ye be found even to fight against

00:31:35.560 --> 00:31:36.220
God.

00:31:36.780 --> 00:31:43.420
And to him they agreed, and when they had called the apostles, and beaten them, they

00:31:43.420 --> 00:31:49.860
demanded that they should not speak in the name of Jesus, and let them go.

00:31:51.060 --> 00:31:56.880
And they departed from the presence of the council, rejoicing that they were counted

00:31:56.880 --> 00:31:59.620
worthy to suffer shame for his name.

00:32:00.780 --> 00:32:08.540
And daily in the temple, and in every house, they ceased not to teach and preach Jesus

00:32:08.540 --> 00:32:09.500
Christ.

00:32:10.020 --> 00:32:14.340
And in those days, when the number of the

00:32:14.340 --> 00:32:21.500
disciples was multiplied, there arose a murmuring of the Grecians against the Hebrews, because

00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:24.860
their widows were neglected in the daily ministration.

00:32:25.980 --> 00:32:32.600
Then the twelve called the multitude of the disciples unto them, and said, It is not reason

00:32:32.600 --> 00:32:36.540
that we should leave the word of God and serve tables.

00:32:37.440 --> 00:32:43.420
Wherefore, brethren, look ye out among you, seven men of honest report, full of the Holy

00:32:43.420 --> 00:32:47.640
Ghost and wisdom, whom we may appoint over this business.

00:32:48.260 --> 00:32:53.640
But we will give ourselves continually to prayer, and to the ministry of the word.

00:32:55.500 --> 00:33:02.180
And the saying pleased the whole multitude, and they chose Stephen, a man full of faith,

00:33:02.180 --> 00:33:11.740
and of the Holy Ghost, and Philip, and Prochorus, and Nicanor, and Tymon, and Parmenes, and

00:33:11.740 --> 00:33:17.420
Nicholas, a proselyte of Antioch, whom they set before the apostles.

00:33:18.180 --> 00:33:21.760
And when they had prayed, they laid their hands on them.

00:33:22.660 --> 00:33:29.800
And the word of God increased, and the number of the disciples multiplied in Jerusalem greatly.

00:33:30.460 --> 00:33:34.420
And a great company of the priests were obedient to the faith.

00:33:35.580 --> 00:33:42.540
And Stephen, full of faith and power, did great wonders and miracles among the people.

00:33:44.760 --> 00:33:51.180
Then there arose certain of the synagogue, which is called the synagogue of the libertines,

00:33:51.180 --> 00:33:59.000
and Cyrenians and Alexandrians, and of them of Cilicia and of Asia, disputing with Stephen.

00:34:00.060 --> 00:34:04.540
And they were not able to resist the wisdom and the spirit by which he spake.

00:34:05.180 --> 00:34:12.560
Then they suborned men, which said, We have heard him speak blasphemous words against

00:34:12.560 --> 00:34:15.120
Moses and against God.

00:34:15.600 --> 00:34:22.660
And they stirred up the people, and the elders, and the scribes, and came upon him, and caught

00:34:22.660 --> 00:34:30.220
him, and brought him to the council, and set up false witnesses, which said, This man ceaseth

00:34:30.220 --> 00:34:35.920
not to speak blasphemous words against this holy place and the law.

00:34:36.120 --> 00:34:42.780
For we have heard him say that this Jesus of Nazareth shall destroy this place, and

00:34:42.780 --> 00:34:46.660
shall change the customs which Moses delivered us.

00:34:46.920 --> 00:34:53.780
And all that sat in the council, looking steadfastly on him, saw his face as it had been the face

00:34:53.780 --> 00:34:54.820
of an angel.

00:35:14.010 --> 00:35:16.960
Then said the High Priest, Are these things so?

00:35:17.240 --> 00:35:20.740
And he said, Men, brethren, and fathers, hearken!

00:35:21.060 --> 00:35:26.360
The God of glory appeared unto our father Abraham when he was in Mesopotamia, before

00:35:26.360 --> 00:35:32.480
he dwelt in Charon, and said unto him, Get thee out of thy country and from thy kindred,

00:35:32.780 --> 00:35:35.200
and come into the land which I shall show thee.

00:35:35.620 --> 00:35:41.520
Then came he out of the land of the Chaldeans, and dwelt in Charon, and from thence, when

00:35:41.520 --> 00:35:46.800
his father was dead, he removed him into this land wherein ye now dwell.

00:35:47.220 --> 00:35:53.460
And he gave him none inheritance in it, no, not so much as to set his foot on, yet he

00:35:53.880 --> 00:35:59.580
would give it to him for a possession, and to his seed after him, when as yet he had

00:35:59.580 --> 00:36:00.480
no child.

00:36:00.880 --> 00:36:06.740
And God spake on this wise, that his seed should sojourn in a strange land, and that

00:36:06.740 --> 00:36:11.420
they should bring them into bondage and entreat them evil four hundred years.

00:36:11.840 --> 00:36:18.040
And the nation to whom they shall be in bondage will I judge, said God, and after that shall

00:36:18.040 --> 00:36:20.760
they come forth and serve me in this place.

00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:27.160
And he gave him the covenant of circumcision, and so Abraham begat Isaac and circumcised

00:36:27.160 --> 00:36:33.280
him the eighth day, and Isaac begat Jacob, and Jacob begat the twelve patriarchs.

00:36:33.460 --> 00:36:39.520
And the patriarchs, moved with envy, sold Joseph into Egypt, but God was with him and

00:36:39.520 --> 00:36:44.440
delivered him out of all his afflictions, and gave him favor and wisdom in the sight

00:36:44.440 --> 00:36:49.940
of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he made him governor over Egypt and all his house.

00:36:50.480 --> 00:36:55.700
Now there came a dearth over all the land of Egypt and Chanan, and great affliction,

00:36:56.020 --> 00:36:58.440
and our fathers found no sustenance.

00:36:58.720 --> 00:37:03.880
But when Jacob heard that there was corn in Egypt, he sent out our fathers first, and

00:37:03.880 --> 00:37:09.160
at the second time Joseph was made known to his brethren, and Joseph's kindred was made

00:37:09.160 --> 00:37:10.380
known unto Pharaoh.

00:37:11.080 --> 00:37:17.160
Then sent Joseph, and called his father Jacob to him, and all his kindred, three score and

00:37:17.160 --> 00:37:18.320
fifteen souls.

00:37:18.1000 --> 00:37:24.880
So Jacob went down into Egypt, and died, he and our fathers, and were carried over to

00:37:24.880 --> 00:37:30.120
Secum, and laid in the sepulcher that Abraham bought for a sum of money of the sons of Amor,

00:37:30.220 --> 00:37:31.460
the father of Secum.

00:37:32.100 --> 00:37:37.180
But when the time of the promise drew nigh, which God had sworn to Abraham, the people

00:37:37.180 --> 00:37:42.180
grew and multiplied in Egypt, till another king arose which knew not Joseph.

00:37:42.740 --> 00:37:48.500
The same dealt subtly with our kindred, and evil entreated our fathers, so that they cast

00:37:48.500 --> 00:37:51.980
out their young children, to the end they might not live.

00:37:52.480 --> 00:37:58.700
In which time Moses was born, and was exceeding fair, and nourished up in his father's house

00:37:58.700 --> 00:37:59.660
three months.

00:38:00.080 --> 00:38:05.240
And when he was cast out, Pharaoh's daughter took him up, and nourished him for her own

00:38:05.240 --> 00:38:05.680
son.

00:38:05.680 --> 00:38:11.380
And Moses was learned in all the wisdom of the Egyptians, and was mighty in words and

00:38:11.380 --> 00:38:12.080
in deeds.

00:38:12.540 --> 00:38:17.960
And when he was full forty years old, it came into his heart to visit his brethren the children

00:38:17.960 --> 00:38:18.720
of Israel.

00:38:19.180 --> 00:38:25.320
And seeing one of them suffer wrong, he defended him, and avenged him that was oppressed and

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:30.580
smote the Egyptian, for he supposed his brethren would have understood how that God by his

00:38:30.580 --> 00:38:33.1000
hand would deliver them, but they understood not.

00:38:34.500 --> 00:38:39.780
And the next day he showed himself unto them as they strove, and would have set them at

00:38:39.780 --> 00:38:41.020
one again, saying,

00:38:41.640 --> 00:38:45.920
"'Sirs ye our brethren, why do ye wrong one to another?'

00:38:45.920 --> 00:38:49.780
But he that did his neighbor wrong thrust him away, saying,

00:38:49.820 --> 00:38:52.880
"'Who made thee a ruler and a judge over us?

00:38:53.240 --> 00:38:57.240
Wilt thou kill me as thou didst the Egyptian yesterday?'

00:38:57.240 --> 00:39:02.960
Then fled Moses at this saying, and was a stranger in the land of Median, where he beget

00:39:02.960 --> 00:39:03.860
two sons.

00:39:04.360 --> 00:39:09.800
And when forty years were expired, there appeared to him in the wilderness of Mount Sinai an

00:39:09.800 --> 00:39:12.620
angel of the Lord in a flame of fire in a bush.

00:39:13.140 --> 00:39:18.640
When Moses saw it, he wondered at the sight, and as he drew near to behold it, the voice

00:39:18.640 --> 00:39:20.800
of the Lord came unto him, saying,

00:39:20.820 --> 00:39:25.840
"'I am the God of thy fathers, the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the God

00:39:25.840 --> 00:39:27.040
of Jacob.'

00:39:27.040 --> 00:39:30.080
Then Moses trembled, and durst not behold.

00:39:30.820 --> 00:39:32.320
Then said the Lord to him,

00:39:32.680 --> 00:39:37.420
"'Put off thy shoes from thy feet, for the place where thou standest is holy ground.

00:39:37.900 --> 00:39:43.480
I have seen, I have seen the affliction of my people, which is in Egypt, and I have heard

00:39:43.480 --> 00:39:46.640
their groaning, and am come down to deliver them.

00:39:46.880 --> 00:39:50.440
And now come, I will send thee into Egypt.'

00:39:50.440 --> 00:39:53.120
This Moses whom they refused, saying,

00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:55.300
Who made thee a ruler and a judge?

00:39:55.660 --> 00:40:00.680
The same did God send to be a ruler and a deliverer by the hand of the angel which appeared

00:40:00.680 --> 00:40:01.820
to him in the bush.

00:40:02.500 --> 00:40:07.680
He brought them out, after that he had showed wonders and signs in the land of Egypt, and

00:40:07.680 --> 00:40:10.900
in the Red Sea, and in the wilderness forty years.

00:40:11.520 --> 00:40:14.920
This is that Moses which said unto the children of Israel,

00:40:15.220 --> 00:40:20.740
"'A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you, of your brethren, like unto me,

00:40:21.060 --> 00:40:23.080
him shall ye hear.'

00:40:23.080 --> 00:40:28.460
This is he that was in the church in the wilderness with the angel which spake to him in the

00:40:28.460 --> 00:40:35.680
Mount Sinai, and with our fathers, who received the lively oracles to give unto us, to whom

00:40:35.680 --> 00:40:40.880
our fathers would not obey but thrust him from them, and in their hearts turned back

00:40:40.880 --> 00:40:47.820
again into Egypt, saying unto Aaron, Make us gods to go before us, for as for this Moses

00:40:47.820 --> 00:40:53.180
which brought us out of the land of Egypt, we want not what has become of him.'

00:40:53.180 --> 00:40:58.880
And they made a calf in those days, and offered sacrifice unto the idol, and rejoiced in the

00:40:58.880 --> 00:41:00.260
works of their own hands.

00:41:00.800 --> 00:41:05.880
Then God turned and gave them up to worship the host of heaven, as it is written in the

00:41:05.880 --> 00:41:12.120
Book of the Prophets, O ye house of Israel, have ye offered to me slain beasts and sacrifices

00:41:12.120 --> 00:41:14.700
by the space of forty years in the wilderness?

00:41:14.700 --> 00:41:20.700
Yea, ye took up the tabernacle of Moloch, and the star of your God Remphan, figures

00:41:20.700 --> 00:41:22.620
which ye made to worship them.

00:41:22.900 --> 00:41:25.780
And I will carry you away beyond Babylon.

00:41:26.380 --> 00:41:32.080
Our fathers had the tabernacle of witness in the wilderness, as he had appointed, speaking

00:41:32.080 --> 00:41:37.780
unto Moses, that he should make it according to the fashion that he had seen, which also

00:41:37.780 --> 00:41:43.260
our fathers, that came after, brought in with Jesus into the possession of the Gentiles,

00:41:43.260 --> 00:41:48.860
whom God drove out before the face of our fathers, unto the days of David, who found

00:41:48.860 --> 00:41:53.280
favor before God, and desired to find a tabernacle for the God of Jacob.

00:41:53.900 --> 00:41:56.200
But Solomon built him in house.

00:41:56.740 --> 00:42:02.580
Howbeit the Most High dwelleth not in temples made with hands, as saith the prophet, Heaven

00:42:02.580 --> 00:42:04.980
is my throne, and earth is my footstool.

00:42:05.360 --> 00:42:10.040
What house will ye build me, saith the Lord, or what is the place of my rest?

00:42:10.040 --> 00:42:13.040
Hath not my hand made all these things?

00:42:13.880 --> 00:42:19.840
Ye stiff-necked and uncircumcised in heart and ears, ye do always resist the Holy Ghost,

00:42:20.060 --> 00:42:22.660
as your fathers did, so do ye.

00:42:23.100 --> 00:42:28.080
Which of the prophets have not your fathers persecuted, and they have slain them which

00:42:28.080 --> 00:42:33.480
showed before of the coming of the Just One, of whom ye have been now the betrayers and

00:42:33.480 --> 00:42:40.160
murderers, who have received the law by the disposition of angels, and have not kept it?

00:42:40.700 --> 00:42:45.240
When they heard these things, they were cut to the heart, and they gnashed on him with

00:42:45.240 --> 00:42:46.080
their teeth.

00:42:46.600 --> 00:42:52.520
But he, being full of the Holy Ghost, looked up steadfastly into heaven, and saw the glory

00:42:52.520 --> 00:42:58.780
of God, and Jesus standing on the right hand of God, and said, Behold, I see the heavens

00:42:58.780 --> 00:43:02.220
opened, and the Son of Man standing on the right hand of God.

00:43:02.880 --> 00:43:07.920
Then they cried out with a loud voice, and stopped their ears, and ran upon him with

00:43:07.920 --> 00:43:14.080
one accord, and cast him out of the city, and stoned him, and the witnesses laid down

00:43:14.080 --> 00:43:17.560
their clothes at a young man's feet, whose name was Saul.

00:43:18.080 --> 00:43:24.080
And they stoned Stephen, calling upon God, and saying, Lord Jesus, receive my spirit.

00:43:24.620 --> 00:43:30.360
And he kneeled down, and cried with a loud voice, Lord, lay not this sin to their charge.

00:43:30.720 --> 00:43:33.600
And when he had said this, he fell asleep.

00:43:36.260 --> 00:43:41.480
And Saul was consenting unto his death, and at that time there was a great persecution

00:43:41.480 --> 00:43:46.560
against the church which was at Jerusalem, and they were all scattered abroad throughout

00:43:46.560 --> 00:43:50.560
the regions of Judea and Samaria, except the apostles.

00:43:51.080 --> 00:43:56.420
And devout men carried Stephen to his burial, and made great lamentation over him.

00:43:56.420 --> 00:44:02.700
As for Saul, he made havoc of the church, entering into every house, and howling men

00:44:02.700 --> 00:44:04.740
and women committed them to prison.

00:44:05.420 --> 00:44:09.480
Therefore, they that were scattered abroad went everywhere preaching the word.

00:44:10.060 --> 00:44:14.820
Then Philip went down to the city of Samaria, and preached Christ unto them.

00:44:15.160 --> 00:44:20.420
And the people, with one accord, gave heed unto those things which Philip spake, hearing

00:44:20.420 --> 00:44:22.640
and seeing the miracles which he did.

00:44:23.040 --> 00:44:28.240
For unclean spirits, crying with loud voice, came out of many that were possessed with

00:44:28.240 --> 00:44:32.880
them, and many taken with palsies, and that were lame, were healed.

00:44:33.400 --> 00:44:35.660
And there was great joy in that city.

00:44:36.280 --> 00:44:41.940
But there was a certain man, called Simon, which before time in the same city used sorcery,

00:44:42.200 --> 00:44:47.760
and bewitched the people of Samaria, giving out that himself was some great one, to whom

00:44:47.760 --> 00:44:52.1000
they all gave heed, from the least to the greatest, saying, This man is the great power

00:44:52.1000 --> 00:44:53.740
of God.

00:44:54.020 --> 00:44:59.700
And to him they had regard, because that of long time he had bewitched them with sorceries.

00:45:00.220 --> 00:45:04.700
But when they believed Philip, preaching the things concerning the kingdom of God, and

00:45:04.700 --> 00:45:08.720
the name of Jesus Christ, they were baptized both men and women.

00:45:09.220 --> 00:45:11.700
Then Simon himself believed also.

00:45:11.940 --> 00:45:17.080
And when he was baptized, he continued with Philip, and wondered, beholding the miracles

00:45:17.080 --> 00:45:18.660
and signs which were done.

00:45:19.300 --> 00:45:24.360
Now when the apostles which were at Jerusalem heard that Samaria had received the word of

00:45:24.360 --> 00:45:30.660
God, they sent unto them Peter and John, who, when they were come down, prayed for them,

00:45:30.860 --> 00:45:36.580
that they might receive the Holy Ghost, for as yet he was fallen upon none of them, only

00:45:36.580 --> 00:45:39.180
they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.

00:45:39.760 --> 00:45:43.1000
Then laid they their hands on them, and they received the Holy Ghost.

00:45:43.1000 --> 00:45:49.600
And when Simon saw that through laying on of the apostles hands the Holy Ghost was given,

00:45:49.980 --> 00:45:56.180
he offered them money, saying, Give me also this power, that on whomsoever I lay hands,

00:45:56.500 --> 00:45:58.200
he may receive the Holy Ghost.

00:45:58.680 --> 00:46:04.320
But Peter said unto him, Thy money perish with thee, because thou hast thought that

00:46:04.320 --> 00:46:06.900
the gift of God may be purchased with money.

00:46:06.900 --> 00:46:12.900
Thou hast neither part nor lot in this matter, for thy heart is not right in the sight of

00:46:12.900 --> 00:46:13.320
God.

00:46:13.980 --> 00:46:19.300
Repent therefore of this thy wickedness, and pray God if perhaps the thought of thine heart

00:46:19.300 --> 00:46:24.700
may be forgiven thee, for I perceive that thou art in the gall of bitterness and in

00:46:24.700 --> 00:46:26.040
the bond of iniquity.

00:46:26.700 --> 00:46:32.040
Then answered Simon and said, Pray ye to the Lord for me, that none of these things which

00:46:32.040 --> 00:46:34.040
ye have spoken come upon me.

00:46:34.640 --> 00:46:39.780
And they, when they had testified and preached the word of the Lord, returned to Jerusalem

00:46:39.780 --> 00:46:43.600
and preached the gospel in many villages of the Samaritans.

00:46:44.680 --> 00:46:50.160
And the angel of the Lord spake unto Philip, saying, Arise and go toward the south unto

00:46:50.160 --> 00:46:54.480
the way that goeth down from Jerusalem unto Gaza, which is desert.

00:46:54.980 --> 00:46:56.600
And he arose and went.

00:46:56.900 --> 00:47:02.520
And behold, a man of Ethiopia, and eunuch of great authority under Candace, queen of

00:47:02.520 --> 00:47:07.880
the Ethiopians, who had the charge of all her treasure and had come to Jerusalem for

00:47:07.880 --> 00:47:13.660
to worship, was returning and sitting in his chariot read Isaias the prophet.

00:47:14.340 --> 00:47:19.400
Then the spirit said unto Philip, Go near and join thyself to this chariot.

00:47:19.960 --> 00:47:26.380
And Philip ran thither to him and heard him read the prophet Isaias, and said, Understandest

00:47:26.380 --> 00:47:27.860
thou what thou readest?

00:47:27.860 --> 00:47:32.400
And he said, How can I except some man should guide me?

00:47:32.640 --> 00:47:36.020
And he desired Philip that he would come up and sit with him.

00:47:36.740 --> 00:47:42.060
The place of the scripture which he read was this, He was led as a sheep to the slaughter,

00:47:42.460 --> 00:47:46.860
and like a lamb done before his shearer, so opened he not his mouth.

00:47:47.240 --> 00:47:52.900
In his humiliation his judgment was taken away, and who shall declare his generation,

00:47:53.340 --> 00:47:55.580
for his life is taken from the earth.

00:47:56.220 --> 00:48:01.800
And the eunuch answered Philip, and said, I pray thee, of whom speaketh the prophet this,

00:48:01.1000 --> 00:48:04.320
of himself or of some other man?

00:48:04.720 --> 00:48:10.560
Then Philip opened his mouth, and began at the same scripture, and preached unto him Jesus.

00:48:11.240 --> 00:48:14.900
And as they went on their way, they came unto a certain water.

00:48:15.200 --> 00:48:20.600
And the eunuch said, See, here is water, what doth hinder me to be baptized?

00:48:20.600 --> 00:48:25.860
And Philip said, If thou believest with all thine heart, thou mayest.

00:48:26.060 --> 00:48:30.640
And he answered and said, I believe that Jesus Christ is the Son of God.

00:48:31.100 --> 00:48:35.1000
And he commanded the chariot to stand still, and they went down both into the water,

00:48:36.260 --> 00:48:39.500
both Philip and the eunuch, and he baptized him.

00:48:39.920 --> 00:48:44.580
And when they were come up out of the water, the Spirit of the Lord caught away Philip,

00:48:45.020 --> 00:48:49.540
that the eunuch saw him no more, and he went on his way rejoicing.

00:48:50.100 --> 00:48:53.920
But Philip was found at Azotes, and passing through,

00:48:54.220 --> 00:48:57.540
he preached in all the cities, till he came to Caesarea.
